                            <comment id="103131" author="thomasd" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 02:40:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Ryan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks for reporting this.&lt;br/&gt;
I think this is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-925&quot; title=&quot;MappingMongoConverterParser is incorrectly rejecting field-naming-strategy-ref XML configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAMONGO-925&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAMONGO-925&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - would you mind giving the provided solution a spin?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
Thomas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103268" author="ryantenney" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 21:31:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The solution works, however I believe it overlooks the cause of this issue, which is that the &quot;abbreviate-field-names&quot; attribute defaults to false. I&apos;ve opened a new pull request which resolves the issue by removing the default value from the offending field.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103574" author="olivergierke" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 08:09:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I took Ryan&apos;s PR and applied a slightly modified version of Thomas&apos; PR on top. We now only explicitly reject the case in which a custom strategy is defined &lt;b&gt;and&lt;/b&gt; abbreviation is activated, as this is the only really invalid case anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
